oracle.pg.common.csvconverter

Class CSV2OPGConfig

  • java.lang.Object
    • oracle.pg.common.csvconverter.CSV2OPGConfigBase
      • oracle.pg.common.csvconverter.CSV2OPEConfig
        • oracle.pg.common.csvconverter.CSV2OPGConfig

  • public class CSV2OPGConfig
extends CSV2OPEConfig
    This class contains the ID configuration settings to convert a CSV file into graph file in Oracle Flat-file format (OPV, OPE files).

      • getVidColumnNames

        public java.lang.String[] getVidColumnNames()
        Getter for the array of column names that will be used as VIDs. If the given columns do not have a numeric value, the value will be hashed into a long number for the ID.
        Returns:
        vidColumnNames

      • keepsOriginalID

        public boolean keepsOriginalID()
        Getter for the keepOriginalID property. If set to true each vertex will have a property with its original Id as the value. This is useful when your Ids are not numeric and they get hashed.
        Returns:
        keepOriginalID
